Explanation:

The problem involves finding the earliest and latest rounds in which the given players (firstPlayer and secondPlayer) compete against each other. We can solve this problem using a while loop and two integer arrays to store the round numbers.

1. Initialize two integer arrays, rounds[0] and rounds[1], to store the round numbers.
2. Check if firstPlayer is greater than secondPlayer. If yes, update rounds[0] and rounds[1] accordingly.
3. If firstPlayer is not greater than secondPlayer, update rounds[0] and rounds[1] accordingly.
4. Continue the while loop until firstPlayer >= secondPlayer.
5. Return the rounds array.

The time complexity is O(log(n) because the loop runs log(n) times, where n is the total number of players. The space complexity is O(1) because we only use a single integer array to store the round numbers. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only requires a small amount of energy to execute.

